The paper deals with the problem of assigning robots to guard perimeters, which is a robotics problem and falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). The problem involves optimization and algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Computational Geometry (cs.CG). The use of autonomous agents and optimization techniques also suggests that it could belong to the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
